I was just watching a [YouTube video on spherical
wheels](https://youtu.be/zKLMCO0-How) composed of independently
rotating hemispheres in order to be able to roll in one direction
controlled by a drive axle and a second direction freely; the guy
built a vehicle with three such wheels that could move in any
direction.  In the center of each hemisphere he included an additional
wheel.  And it occurred to me: what about a toroidal wheel?

Not such a novel idea, I guess, with the diagonal rollers.  But what if 
